Key Match Events: Joey Veerman scored the opening goal for the Netherlands in the fourth minute.
Maximilian Mittelstadt equalized for Germany in the 10th minute with a thunderbolt from distance.
Niclas Fullkrug scored the winning goal for Germany after connecting to a Toni Kroos corner.
Post-Match Reflections: Julian Nagelsmann's Germany will be a force to reckon with in Euro 2024 preparations.
Ronald Koeman will be disappointed with his team's finishing.
Others: It was Fullkrug's 11th international goal in just 15 appearances.
Musiala was the brightest spark on the pitch, displaying a wide range of skills and maturity.
Kai Havertz was an almost anonymous figure and was replaced in the 73rd minute by Fullkrug.
